== Verifier

The verifier walks the captured MP135 UART stream
(`streams/mp135.uart.bin`) for the bench summary line that the
firmware prints once the streaming read has been validated against
the incrementing pattern. The line carries `<mode> in <ms> ms` plus
elapsed time, effective Mbps, a `firsterr=<offset>` field that is
`-1` only when every byte matched, and an `auto=on` flag that the
stream-pattern helper requires. The verifier prints the configured
SCLK, firmware effective Mbps, test-server wall time between the
`bench_start` and `bench_done` marks, and a wall-rate computed from
requested payload bits divided by measured wall time next to each
prescaler result. The mission target is the first STRICT block:
`check_stream_wall_rate_at_least("quad", 7, 200.0, 33554432,
wall_floor_mbps=200.0)` -- gates on CRC + firsterr=-1 + chunk
shape + auto=on, then asserts wall rate >=200 Mbps from the
bench_start/bench_done marks divided into 33554432 bytes.

The slow-prescaler blocks pass an explicit small `wall_floor_mbps`
(2.0 Mbps for presc=203, 5.0 Mbps for presc=63) to override the
default 90%-of-physical floor; that floor is intended for the
mission target and would spuriously fail at low rates whose physical
ceiling already exceeds the small absolute threshold by orders of
magnitude.

The helpers (`STREAM_RE`, `_stream_pick`, `_stream_rates`,
`_stream_rate_text`, `check_stream_pattern`,
`check_stream_wall_rate_at_least`, `check_raw_read_pattern`,
`_bench_wall_ms`, `_check_rates_with_clock`,
`_check_physical_floor`, `_check_physical_ceiling`,
`_physical_max_mbps`, `STREAM_EFFECTIVE_RATE_FLOOR`,
`STREAM_WALL_RATE_FLOOR`, `QSPI_KER_HZ`) are copied verbatim from
the `verify.py` chunk in `src/spi_1lane_stream.nw`. The four
diagnostic helpers (0x6C/0x6D/0x6E/0x6F) are kept from the prior
spi_quad.nw verbatim. Bench `b`/`q` helpers are dropped: this
chapter no longer uses the polled FIFO path.

