== Test runner

`build/spi_quad/Makefile` is the entry point invoked from
`cd build/spi_quad && make test`. It re-tangles the plan and the
verifier from `src/spi_quad.nw` so an edit to this chapter is picked
up on the next test run, then hands off to the shared `run_md.py`
driver pointed at by `$TEST_SERV`.

The chapter introduces no new RTL: `bitstreams` depends on the
canonical `qspi.bin` produced under `build/qspi/` (the spi chapter's
`bitstreams` target also stages it via the same path), and `qspi.bin`
is symlinked into the chapter's build directory. `flash.tsv` and
`main.stm32` are the same MP135 host artifacts the spi chapter uses,
symlinked from the MP135 baremetal qspi build tree. `sim` is a no-op
for this chapter.

<<Makefile>>=
NW := ../../src/spi_quad.nw
MP135_QSPI_DIR := /home/claude/stm32mp135_test_board/baremetal/qspi/build
MP135_QSPI_SRC := /home/claude/stm32mp135_test_board/baremetal/qspi

.PHONY: all test bitstreams sim bitstream
all: TEST.md verify.py qspi.bin spi_quad.bin flash.tsv main.stm32

Makefile: $(NW)
	tangle Makefile < $<

test: all bitstreams
	python3 -u $$TEST_SERV/run_md.py --fresh --ledger ledger.txt --module spi_quad --log run_md.log

bitstreams: qspi.bin spi_quad.bin

bitstream: bitstreams

sim:

TEST.md: $(NW)
	tangle TEST.md < $<

verify.py: $(NW)
	tangle verify.py < $<

qspi.bin:
	$(MAKE) -C ../.. build/qspi/qspi.bin
	ln -sf ../qspi/qspi.bin $@

spi_quad.bin:
	$(MAKE) -C ../.. build/spi/spi_quad.bin
	ln -sf ../spi/spi_quad.bin $@

flash.tsv:
	ln -sf $(MP135_QSPI_SRC)/flash.tsv $@

main.stm32:
	ln -sf $(MP135_QSPI_DIR)/main.stm32 $@
@

<<spi_quad.mk>>=
# spi_quad: no new RTL. The bitstreams are qspi.bin (framing slave,
# legacy) and spi_quad.bin (simple raw streaming slave from spi.nw
# with LANES=4) built under build/qspi/ and build/spi/ respectively.
# We expose them inside build/spi_quad/ via symlinks so the
# in-build-dir Makefile can resolve them relatively.

build/spi_quad/qspi.bin: build/qspi/qspi.bin | build/spi_quad
	ln -sf ../qspi/qspi.bin $@

build/spi_quad/spi_quad.bin: build/spi/spi_quad.bin | build/spi_quad
	ln -sf ../spi/spi_quad.bin $@

build/spi_quad/flash.tsv: | build/spi_quad
	ln -sf $(MP135_QSPI_SRC)/flash.tsv $@

build/spi_quad/main.stm32: | build/spi_quad
	ln -sf $(MP135_QSPI_DIR)/main.stm32 $@

bitstream: build/spi_quad/qspi.bin build/spi_quad/spi_quad.bin
@

== Summary

Cycle 2 iter 38 strategy: change iCE40 SB_IO PIN_TYPE on quad
IO[3:0] from 6'b101001 (PIN_OUTPUT_TRISTATE) to 6'b101101 to add a
registered output stage for tighter timing margin, then test three
low-rate quad nibble diagnostics (0x6C/0x6E/0x6F at presc=203) to
confirm the basic data path still works, followed by two STRICT
mission blocks (presc=5 sshift=0 primary, presc=7 sshift=0 backup)
each running 32 MiB auto-stream and gating on the firmware summary
sentinel `, firsterr=-1`. Mission accomplished if either STRICT
block passes.
